social welfare in china in the context of three transitions siepr siepr stanford institute for economic policy research search the site enter your keywords main links home about siepr research at siepr education at siepr events at siepr people at siepr publications at siepr economics in the news support siepr contact us stay connected stay connected banner home publications profile display social welfare in china in the context of three transitions type scid working paper 66 author s athar hussain published 08 1 00 region china download pdf abstract this paper conducts a comprehensive review and evaluation of china's social welfare development in the context of socio economic changes characterized by three transitions the analysis first focuses on the urban and rural social security systems by examining the arrangements for income maintenance in old age and unemployment as well as the effectiveness of such provisions this paper goes on to describe the current status of healthcare provision in urban and rural areas and explore ways to finance adequate medical care and eradicate preventable illnesses finally the paper identifies the major impediments in the implementation of social security reforms aimed at replacing the inherited system stanford university economics department stanford center for international development public policy program site map economic summit
